    { "kind": 1, "languageId": "markdown", "value": "------", "output": [], "executionSummary": {} },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "## Part 1: Store `WindTurbine` data in state",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "In <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx</code></a>, import `useState` from React. This allows us to save the turbines to state variables.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "languageId": "typescriptreact",
      "value": "/*\n  WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n*/\n// import React from 'react';\n// ...\n// import { useEffect } from 'react';\nimport { useState } from 'react';",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "Use the `useState` hook to declare the state variable, `turbines`, to save the turbines to state.\n\nDeclare it at the top of <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx</code></a>, like in the following code cell:",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "languageId": "typescriptreact",
      "value": "/*\n  WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n*/\n\n// const WindTurbineHomePage = () => {\n\n    const [turbines, setTurbines] = useState([]);\n\n  // useEffect(() => {\n  //   const loadTurbines = async () => {\n  //   ...",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    { "kind": 1, "languageId": "markdown", "value": "------", "output": [], "executionSummary": {} },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "## Part 2: Save Turbines to State",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "Let's save the WindTurbines stored in `turbineData` to the state using the `setTurbines` function. That way, we can re-render the component with the fetched data and display them with markers.\n\nInside the `try` block of the `loadTurbines` function, add the following line to save the fetched data to state:",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "languageId": "typescriptreact",
      "value": "/*\n  WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n*/\n\n// useEffect(() => {\n//   // Fetch wind turbine data using CRUD method\n//   const loadTurbines = async () => {\n//     try {\n//       const turbineData = await fetchAllTurbines();\n//       console.log('Success:', turbineData);\n         setTurbines(turbineData); // Store the fetched data in state\n\n//     } catch (error) {\n//       console.error('Error fetching wind turbine data:', error);\n//     } \n//   };\n//   loadTurbines();\n// }, []);",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    { "kind": 1, "languageId": "markdown", "value": "------", "output": [], "executionSummary": {} },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "## Part 3: Render Turbine Markers",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "Now that the turbine data is saved to state, we can plot these turbines on the map.\n\nAdd the following import statements to <a href=\"../../ui/c3/src/customInstances/WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\"><code>WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx</code></a>:",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "languageId": "typescriptreact",
      "value": "/*\n  WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n*/\n\n// import React from 'react';\n// ...\n// import { useState } from 'react';\nimport { windTurbineIcon } from '@c3/app/ui/src/components/icons/MapIcons'; // Import the wind turbine icon\nimport { Marker } from 'react-leaflet'; // Import the Marker component from react-leaflet",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "Replace the existing <MapContainer> component with the following code snippet.\n\nFor each WindTurbine object in `turbines`, the new code creates a `<Marker>` at each turbine's geographic coordinates.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "languageId": "typescriptreact",
      "value": "/*\n  WindTurbine.HomePage.tsx\n*/\n\n// ...\n\n//return (\n// <>\n  // <MapContainer \n  //   center={[39.8, -98.5]} \n  //   zoom={4} \n  //   className=\"map-container\" \n  //   zoomControl={false}\n  //   {...{} as any}>\n  //   <ZoomControl position=\"bottomleft\" />\n\n    // {/* OpenStreetMap Tile Layer */}\n    // <TileLayer\n    //     url=\"https://{s}.basemaps.cartocdn.com/light_all/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png\"\n    //     attribution='&copy; <a href=\"https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright\">OpenStreetMap</a> contributors &copy; <a href=\"https://carto.com/attributions\">CARTO</a>'\n    //       {...{} as any}\n    // />\n\n    {/* Wind Turbine Markers */}\n    {(turbines).map((turbine) => ( // Render markers for each turbine\n      <Marker  \n        key={turbine.id} \n        position={[turbine.latitude, turbine.longitude]} \n        icon={windTurbineIcon}\n        {...{} as any}> {/* This avoids the prop warning for using an older version of React */ }\n      </Marker>\n    ))}\n  // </MapContainer>\n  // </>\n// );",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    { "kind": 1, "languageId": "markdown", "value": "### Verify result", "output": [], "executionSummary": {} },
    {
      "kind": 1,
